description: From Ecclesiastical Latin [Term?], from Ancient Greek ἀναγωγή (anagōgḗ, “religious or ecstatic elevation, mystical feeling”), from ἀνάγειν (anágein, “lift up”), from ἀνά (aná, “up”) + ἄγειν (ágein, “to lead”).

entries.meaning: The spiritual or mystical interpretation of a word or passage beyond the literal, allegorical or moral sense.
